{"title_page": "Kabali Vishwanth", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Indian film actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          =  Kabali Vishwanth\n| image         =\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       = \n| birth_name     = \n| birth_date     =\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| occupation    = [[Film actor]]\n| yearsactive   = 2010\u2013present \n| spouse        = \n| website      = \n}}\n'''Kabali Vishwanth''' is an Indian [[film actor]] who has appeared in Tamil language films. After appearing in small supporting roles and working as an assistant choreographer, he made his breakthrough as an actor with a supporting role in [[Pa. Ranjith]]'s ''[[Kabali (film)|Kabali]]'' (2016).\n\n== Career ==\nVishwanath started his career playing an anti-hero in [[S. A. Chandrasekhar]]'s ''[[Veluthu Kattu]]'' (2010). He then portrayed small supporting roles in films including as [[Arun Vijay]]'s friend in ''[[Thadaiyara Thaakka]]'' (2012), as [[Attakathi Dinesh|Dinesh]]'s elder brother in ''[[Attakathi]]'' (2012), and as Prakash Raj's neighbour in ''[[Dhoni (film)|Dhoni]]'' (2012). He later moved on to assist dance choreographer [[Sridhar (choreographer)|Sridhar]] in films.<ref>{{Cite new|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-dont-want-to-be-boxed-Vishwanath/articleshow/53154725.cms|title=I don't want to be boxed: Vishwanath|work=The Times of India|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desimartini.com/news/tamil/i-prefer-doing-different-types-of-character-vishwanath-article34734.htm|title=I Prefer Doing Different Types Of Character: Vishwanath|date=12 July 2016|website=Desimartini|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nVishwanath made a breakthrough as an actor after portraying a role in [[Pa. Ranjith]]'s ''[[Kabali (film)|Kabali]]'' (2016), which starred [[Rajinikanth]] in the lead role. The film saw him credited as Vishwanth, and he subsequently kept the name for his future work. Portraying a Chennai-based gangster hired to protect Rajinikanth's lead character, the film and his role won acclaim.<ref name = te>{{Cite new|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/im-learning-a-lot-from-vikram-viswanath/articleshow/59773985.cms|title=I\u2019m learning a lot from Vikram: Viswanath|work=The Times of India|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> The high-profile nature of the film prompted several film makers to sign him on for their productions, and notably later worked on ''[[Sketch (2018 film)|Sketch]]'' (2018) alongside [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]] and [[N. Linguswamy|Linguswamy]]'s ''[[Sandakozhi 2]]'' (2018), portraying the husband of [[Varalaxmi Sarathkumar]]'s character.<ref name = te/><ref>{{Cite new|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2017/nov/28/kabali-star-vishwanath-in-sandakozhi-2-3282.html|title=Kabali star Vishwanath in Sandakozhi 2|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desimartini.com/news/tamil/kollywood-actor-vishwanth-talks-about-his-roles-in-the-upcoming-movies-article68285.htm|title=Kollywood Actor Vishwanth Talks About His Roles In The Upcoming Movies|date=21 November 2017|website=Desimartini|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> He also worked on a Hindi-language film as well as portraying his first lead role in the horror-comedy, ''Onaaigal Jakkiradhai'' (2018).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/attakathi-kabali-actor-vishwanth-to-act-in-bollywood-film-directed-by-debutant-sajos-tamil-news-168814|title='Kabali' actor Bollywood bound - Tamil News|date=9 October 2016|website=IndiaGlitz.com|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n